mbly - **Phase 6** (Days 6-7): QA & Launch ## Expected Output - 500+ assets (sales pages, blogs, emails, videos, workflows) - 75,000+ words of content - 20+ lead magnets - 15+ automation workflows - 3 complete knowledge bases --- Last Updated: 2026-04-10 Status: READY FOR DEPLOYMENT \"\"\", \"MASTER_EXECUTION_GUIDE.md\": \"\"\"# Master Execution Guide - Pilot Mastery Academy ## Pre-Execution Checklist - [ ] GitHub repo created (or using ZIP) - [ ] Cursor IDE or Claude Cowork installed - [ ] Claude API key configured (if using Make/Zapier) - [ ] Domain registered (pilotmasteryacademy.com) - [ ] Stripe account set up - [ ] Budget allocated ($3-5K for ads, tools) ## Execution Options ### Option 1: Cursor IDE (Recommended for Single Developer) 1. Open Cursor 2. File → Open Folder → Select `pilot-mastery-academy/` 3. Cursor will auto-load `.cursorrules` 4. Open `instructions/00_MAIN_BUILD_INSTRUCTION.md` 5. Run the master command: ```bash claude build --project pilot-mastery-academy --execution-mode parallel --phases all --agents 9 --tasks 26 Copy Option 2: Claude Cowork (Recommended for Team) Go to Claude.ai → Cowork tab Click \"New Project\" → \"Import from GitHub\" Enter: https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/pilot-mastery-academy.git Cowork will load all files with persistent memory Use the /build command with parameters: Copy /build project=pilot-mastery-academy phases=all error-strategy=auto-correct reporting=detailed Option 3: Claude Web (Simplest) Go to Claude.ai Upload instructions/00_MAIN_BUILD_INSTRUCTION.md + all PRD files Type: \"Execute the full Pilot Mastery Academy build system with error correction\" Phase-by-Phase Breakdown Phase 1: Content Generation (12-16 hours) Goal: 75,000+ words across all offers Tasks: Sales pages, email sequences, blog outlines, scripts Output: 45 content files Validation: Spell-check, plagiarism-check, brand consistency, tone audit Phase 2: SEO & Metadata (8-10 hours) Goal: 100+ keywords mapped, 200+ meta descriptions Tasks: Keyword