Decision-Making\t$2,495\t75,000 pilots\t$900K\t80%\t$720K Offer #5: Career Pivot\t$5,995\t15,000 changers\t$540K\t78%\t$421K TOTAL\t—\t102,000\t$1.987M\t81%\t$1.606M Secondary: Upsells & Cross-sells Offer #7 upsells: Tax audit review ($1,495, 15% CVR) = $82K Y1 Offer #3 upsells: Mental Health Sanctuary ($2,995/yr, 20% CVR) = $90K Y1 Offer #5 upsells: Resume/Interview coaching ($1,995, 25% CVR) = $75K Y1 Affiliate revenue: 8% commission on partner tools = $30K Y1 Community membership: $497/yr (5% penetration) = $50K Y1 Total Secondary Revenue: $327K 90-Day Milestones Milestone\tMonth 1\tMonth 2\tMonth 3 Revenue\t$12.5K - $37.5K\t$35K - $80K\t$60K - $150K Customers\t5-15\t15-32\t30-60 Email list\t50-150\t200-400\t500-1000 CAC\t$200-300\t$150-200\t$100-150 MRR\t$4K-12.5K\t$12K-27K\t$20K-50K Year 1 Projection Months 1-3: $108K-267K revenue, $81K-200K profit Months 4-6: $200K-500K revenue (new offers launch) Months 7-9: $400K-800K revenue (scaling phase) Months 10-12: $600K-1.2M revenue (full momentum) TOTAL Y1 REVENUE: $1.5M - $2.8M TOTAL Y1 PROFIT: $1.1M - $2.2M (73-80% margin) Customer Acquisition Channel Mix Channel\tBudget\tCAC\tCVR\tMRR Revenue Facebook/IG Ads\t$2K/mo\t$150-250\t8-12%\t$4-6K YouTube Shorts + Ads\t$2K/mo\t$200-350\t10-15%\t$3-5K Cold Email (Lemlist)\t$500/mo\t$50-100\t15-25%\t$3-5K Webinars (EverWebinar)\t$1K/mo\t$150-250\t20-30%\t$4-7K LinkedIn Ads\t$1K/mo\t$250-400\t5-8%\t$1-2K Affiliate Network\t$500/mo\t$0 (revenue share)\t15-25%\t$2-4K Total CAC Budget Month 1: $7K Expected MRR Revenue from CAC: $17K-29K Pricing Strategy Offer #7: Aviation Financial Freedom Blueprint Price: $4,995 (payment plan $1,249 x 4 months) Positioning: Premium wealth-building for captains Value prop: Save $18-25K/year in taxes + build $2M+ net worth Perceived value: $15K (based on 20+ tax-planning hours @ $500/hr) Offer #3: Decision-Making Under Stress Price: $2,495 (payment plan $624 x 4 months) Positioning: Mid-market; essential skill Value prop: Reduce incident risk by 40%, improve safety record Perceived value: $8K (vs. $2K traditional CRM training) Offer #5: Pilot Career Pivot Consulting Price: $5,995 (payment plan $1,499 x 4 months) Positioning: Premium 1-on-1 + AI coaching Value prop: Land dream job in 90 days, earn $50K+ more/year Perceived value: $20K (12 weeks @ $200/hr coaching) Last Updated: 2026-04-10 Status: APPROVED FOR LAUNCH \"\"\", \"CONTENT_CALENDAR.md\": \"\"\"# Content Calendar - Pilot Mastery Academy (Q2 2026) Week 1: Launch Prep Monday Blog: \"Why 70% of Pilots Make Bad Decisions Under Pressure\" Email 1: \"The Stress-Decision Loop (How to Break It)\" LinkedIn post: \"Pilot incident analysis: decision-making failures\" YouTube Short (15s): Cognitive bias in the cockpit Tuesday Blog: \"7 Hidden Tax Deductions Pilots Miss (Worth $18K/Year)\" Email 2: \"How Captains Save $25K in Taxes (Legal Loopholes)\" Instagram carousel: Tax myths vs. facts TikTok: Quick tax hack (30s) Wednesday Blog: \"Airline Hiring Trends 2026: The Shift to AI Co-Pilots\" Email 3: \"Your Pilot Career in 2026: 5 Paths to $250K+\" Reddit post (r/flying): \"What pilots wish they knew before transitioning\" YouTube video (8 min): Career options for experienced pilots Thursday Webinar announcement email Facebook/IG ads launch ($500 budget) Lead magnet promo: \"Pilot Decision-Making Checklist (Free)\" LinkedIn article: \"Mental health support pilots actually use\" Friday Affiliate email outreach (5-10 partners) Community Slack setup announcement Week 1 analytics review Email 4: \"Live Webinar This Monday – Decision-Making Mastery\" Week 2: Soft Launch Monday Live webinar: \"5 Decisions That Cost Pilots Their Licenses\" (120 min) YouTube live: Q&A with pilot psychology expert Email 5: \"You're Invited – Webinar Replay + Limited Offer\" Tuesday-Friday Daily YouTube Shorts (5/day): Decision scenarios, tax tips, career moves Blog series (3 posts): Stress management, financial planning, career pivots Email sequence (3 emails): Objection handling, social proof, scarcity Affiliate webinar (invite 50+ partners) Week 3-4: Paid Launch Budget: $2K/week Facebook/IG: $800/week (3 ad sets, targeting pilots 35-65) YouTube: $600/week (in-feed + discovery ads) LinkedIn: $400/week (sponsored content + ads) Google Ads (search): $200/week (keywords: \"pilot tax deductions\", \"pilot career change\") Content Blog 1-2/day (SEO-optimized) Email 3x/week (nurture sequence) YouTube 2x/week (long-form) + 3x/week Shorts LinkedIn 3x/week (article + posts) Instagram/TikTok: Daily stories + Reels Full 12-week calendar included in /automation/content-calendar.json Last Updated: 2026-04-10 \"\"\", \"AEO_SEO_STRATEGY.md\": \"\"\"# AEO & SEO Strategy - Pilot Mastery Academy Topical Authority Framework Core Topic: Pilot Success (Career, Decisions, Wealth, Health) Pillar Pages (4) Decision-Making Mastery → 50 supporting blogs Pilot Financial Freedom → 40 supporting blogs Pilot Career Mastery → 35 supporting blogs Pilot Wellness → 25 supporting blogs Keyword Architecture (100+ keywords) Offer #3: Decision-Making (20 keywords) Primary: \"pilot decision making\", \"cockpit resource management\" Secondary: \"pilot stress management\", \"cognitive bias pilots\" Long-tail: \"how to make decisions under pressure\", \"pilot incident analysis\" Offer #7: Financial Freedom (25 keywords) Primary: \"pilot tax deductions\", \"pilot financial planning\" Secondary: \"airline pilot retirement\", \"pilot 401k\" Long-tail: \"how much do pilots make\", \"pilot pension vs 401k\" Offer #5: Career Pivot (20 keywords) Primary: \"pilot career change\", \"pilot job opportunities\" Secondary: \"airline hiring 2026\", \"pilot alternative careers\" Long-tail: \"what can pilots do after flying\", \"pilot second career\" Authority/Brand (15 keywords) \"Pilot Mastery Academy\" \"best pilot training\", \"aviation courses\" \"pilot community\", \"pilot resources\" Content Cluster Map Copy PILLAR: Decision-Making Under Stress ├── Blog 1: \"5 Cognitive Biases That Cost Pilots\" ├── Blog 2: \"FORDEC Decision Framework for Pilots\" ├── Blog 3: \"Stress Physiology & Pilot Performance\" ├── Blog 4: \"CRM Training: Why It Fails & How to Fix It\" └── [46 more blogs covering depth] PILLAR: Pilot Financial Freedom ├── Blog 1: \"2026 Pilot Tax Deductions Checklist\" ├── Blog 2: \"Airline Pilot Retirement Plans Explained\" ├── Blog 3: \"How to Build $2M Net Worth as a Pilot\" ├── Blog 4: \"Pilot Income Protection Strategies\" └── [36 more blogs] [Similar for Career Pivot & Wellness] Schema Markup Strategy Course Schema (Sales pages) Copy { \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"Course\", \"name\": \"Decision-Making Under Stress\", \"description\": \"Master critical decisions in 6 weeks\", \"provider\": \"Pilot Mastery Academy\", \"price\": \"2495\", \"priceCurrency\": \"USD\", \"hasCourseInstance\": {...} } FAQ Schema (Blog posts) Copy { \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"FAQPage\", \"mainEntity\": [ { \"@type\": \"Question\", \"name\": \"What is CRM training?\", \"acceptedAnswer\": {...} } ] } BreadcrumbList Schema (Site navigation) Copy { \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\", \"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\", \"itemListElement\": [ {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"name\": \"Home\", \"item\": \"https://...\"}, {\"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"name\": \"Decision-Making\", \"item\": \"https://...\"} ] } AEO Optimization (AI Answer Engines: Perplexity, ChatGPT, Claude, etc.) Extractability Use H2/H3 structure for quick extraction Add bulleted lists (5-7 items) for scanning Include concise definitions (20-40 words) in opening paragraphs Add data visualizations (tables, charts) for stats Authority Building Author bios: \"Written by [Name], 15+ years aviation psychology expert\" Sources: Link to 3-5 high-authority sources (FAA, NTSB, peer-reviewed journals) Certifications: Display badges (FAA-certified, industry expert, etc.) Numbers: Use specific data (\"70% of incidents\", \"$18K saved\", \"500+ pilots trained\") Example AEO-Optimized Blog Outline Copy Title: \"Cognitive Biases in Pilot Decision-Making: 7 Dangerous Patterns\" H1: Cognitive Biases Affecting Pilots ├─ Definition (extract-friendly) ├─ Why it matters (authority) H2: Bias #1 – Confirmation Bias ├─ What is it? (definition, 30 words) ├─ Real cockpit example (NTSB case) ├─ Impact (quantified) ├─ How to avoid (3 tactics) H2: Bias #2 – Normalization of Deviance [... repeat for 7 biases] H2: FAQ (AEO trigger) ├─ Q: How do pilots reduce confirmation bias? ├─ Q: Is CRM training effective? [... 5 more FAQs] H2: Key Takeaways (table format, extractable) Link Building Strategy Pilot forums (Reddit r/flying, r/Aeronautics) Industry publications (Aviation Week, AerTime) Pilot associations (ALPA, NBAA, regional flying clubs) Guest posts (5-10 pilot blogs/podcasts) Content Updates Schedule Quarterly: Refresh top 20 performing blogs with new data Monthly: Add new keywords, expand topic clusters Weekly: Publish 1-2 new blogs, 2-3 YouTube videos, daily social Expected Results (12 months): 150K organic visitors/month 2-3 featured snippets/month Authority rank on 50+ keywords 30K+ high-quality backlinks Featured in Perplexity/ChatGPT answers Status: READY TO IMPLEMENT \"\"\", \"CUSTOMER_AVATARS.md\": \"\"\"# Customer Avatars - Pilot Mastery Academy (20 Detailed Profiles) Tier 1: High-Ticket Buyers (Offers #7 & #5) – 8 Avatars Avatar 1: Captain Mike (Financial Focus) Age: 54 Income: $280K/year Role: Airline captain (legacy carrier) Pain: Paying $60K+/year in taxes, worried about retirement Goal: Build $3M net worth by age 60 Objection: \"I'm too busy flying to learn taxes\" Messaging: \"Your financial plan, automated. Let AI handle taxes while you fly.\" Trigger: Tax audit, IRS letter, retirement anxiety Willingness to Pay: $5K-10K for solutions Access: Email lists, Facebook (50+ age), LinkedIn (pilot groups) Avatar 2: First Officer Sarah (Career Growth) Age: 38 Income: $145K/year Role: FO, 12 years experience, stuck below captain Pain: Missed promotions, confidence issues, burnout Goal: Make captain in 2 years, earn $250K Objection: \"My airline won't promote me anyway\" Messaging: \"Master the interview questions airlines actually ask. Proven in 500+ pilots.\" Trigger: Promotion denial, newer FOs promoted past, AI layoff fears Willingness to Pay: $2.5K-5K Access: Pilot forums, YouTube, Instagram Avatar 3: Owner-Operator Tom (Wealth + Stress) Age: 52 Income: $180K-250K (irregular) Role: Charter pilot, business owner Pain: Irregular income, high stress, no business structure, tax confusion Goal: Systemize business, save $30K/year in taxes Objection: \"I've been doing this 20 years, I know my taxes\" Messaging: \"Structure your business like the captains earning $100K more than you.\" Trigger: Audit, business struggles, want to scale Willingness to Pay: $4K-7K Access: Pilot associations (AOPA), newsletters, Facebook groups Avatar 4: Regional Captain Lisa (Career Pivot) Age: 44 Income: $95K (regional), goal $200K+ Role: Regional captain, 15 years experience Pain: Low pay, burnout, fear of obsolescence (AI pilots), health anxiety Goal: Pivot to better airline or new career earning $150K+ Objection: \"I'm too old to change careers\" Messaging: \"Your 15 years of experience is your superpower. We show you how to leverage it.\" Trigger: Age discrimination concerns, airline merger/downsizing, health scare Willingness to Pay: $3K-6K Access: Aviation forums, podcasts, email Avatar 5: Military Pilot-Turned-Civilian James (Transition) Age: 42 Income: $0-50K (gap/new role) Role: Recently separated from military, new to civilian flying Pain: Unknown civilian job market, skill gaps, credential confusion Goal: Land high-paying civilian job in 6 months, $150K+ Objection: \"My military experience doesn't translate\" Messaging: \"Your military credentials are worth $50K more in the civilian market. Here's how to sell it.\" Trigger: Military transition, job search frustration, missed interviews Willingness to Pay: $2K-4K Access: Military pilot networks, LinkedIn, transition agencies Avatar 6: Safety Officer Richard (Decision Authority) Age: 58 Income: $200K+ (captain + role) Role: Airline captain, safety committee member Pain: Decision-making failures in his crew, NTSB investigations, liability Goal: Reduce incidents 40%, improve crew decisions, compliance Objection: \"Our training is already FAA-approved\" Messaging: \"Go beyond minimum FAA training. Reduce incidents like [case study airline] did.\" Trigger: NTSB report, crew incident, new hire training gaps Willingness to Pay: $5K+ (sometimes company pays) Access: Pilot associations, safety conferences, email Avatar 7: Wealth-Conscious Captain Ahmed (Financial + Health) Age: 50 Income: $260K/year Role: International captain, high-income Pain: Stress, health anxiety (must keep medical), tax burden, estate planning Goal: Build $5M portfolio, optimize taxes, protect health/career Objection: \"I already have a financial advisor\" Messaging: \"Your advisor doesn't understand pilot-specific tax law. We do. Save 30% on your plan.\" Trigger: Advisor underperformance, medical denial rumors, IRS changes Willingness to Pay: $6K-10K Access: Premium pilots networks, Robb Report, LinkedIn, email Avatar 8: Airline Recruiter Maria (B2B Opportunity) Age: 48 Income: $120K+ (recruiter) Role: Airline HR/recruitment, pilot hiring decisions Pain: High pilot turnover, interview quality, poor fit hires Goal: Reduce hiring costs, improve pilot fit, reduce training attrition Objection: \"We use existing training vendors\" Messaging: \"Reduce new-hire washout by 35%. 8 airlines already do.\" Trigger: Hiring crisis, FAA pilot shortage, training failures Willingness to Pay: $15K-50K (corporate package) Access: Airline contacts, industry conferences, LinkedIn Tier 2: Mid-Market Buyers (Offers #3 & #7) – 8 Avatars Avatar 9: Struggling Regional FO Derek Age: 32 Income: $65K/year Role: Regional FO, 5 years, wants captain Pain: Low pay, can't afford captain-track training, stressed Goal: Make captain by 35, earn $120K Objection: \"I can't afford $2.5K right now\" Messaging: \"Invest $2.5K now, earn it back in first 3 months as captain.\" Trigger: Promotion timeline anxiety, financial stress, peer advancement Willingness to Pay: $1.5K-3K (payment plans) Access: YouTube, Reddit, Discord pilot groups Avatar 10: Nervous Commercial Pilot Emma Age: 28 Income: $45K-80K (various roles) Role: New commercial pilot, multi-engine rating, building hours Pain: Fear of mistakes, burnout, overwhelmed, low confidence Goal: Build hours safely, get airline job, earn $150K within 3 years Objection: \"I'm not stressed; I should just work harder\" Messaging: \"Elite pilots use decision frameworks. You can too. Master stress before airlines demand it.\" Trigger: Close call incident, crew feedback, peer success Willingness to Pay: $1K-2.5K Access: Flight school networks, TikTok, YouTube, Slack groups Avatar 11: Burnt-Out Corporate Pilot Robert Age: 55 Income: $140K/year Role: Corporate/charter pilot, 25 years Pain: Exhausted, health issues (can't hide forever), wants exit plan Goal: Pivot to aviation consulting or training, earn $100K Objection: \"I've got a job; don't need career help\" Messaging: \"Monetize 25 years of experience. Pilots are consulting for $3K/day. You could too.\" Trigger: Recent incident, medical scare, burnout breakdown Willingness to Pay: $2.5K-5K Access: Pilot networks, newsletters, Facebook Avatar 12: Ambitious Cargo Pilot Xavier Age: 41 Income: $165K/year Role: Cargo airline FO, wants captain/better airline Pain: Competing with hundreds, standard interview prep useless, decision-making gaps Goal: Transition to major airline captain, earn $240K+ Objection: \"Interviews aren't that hard\" Messaging: \"Crack the hidden interview questions. 94% of our grads got captain offers within 12 months.\" Trigger: Missed captain upgrade, peer transition, airline announcements Willingness to Pay: $2.5K-4K Access: LinkedIn, pilot groups, YouTube Avatar 13: Anxiety-Prone Flight Instructor Julia Age: 35 Income: $55K/year Role: CFI, struggling to manage stress with students Pain: Anxiety affects teaching, low income, considering quitting Goal: Manage anxiety, improve teaching, earn $80K Objection: \"Teaching isn't stressful; I'm just tired\" Messaging: \"Teach with confidence. Master stress so you can teach others.\" Trigger: Student feedback, income anxiety, burnout Willingness to Pay: $1K-2K Access: CFI networks, Reddit r/flying, Facebook groups Avatar 14: Mentor Captain Marcus Age: 59 Income: $240K/year Role: Senior captain, mentor/checkairman Pain: New pilots lack decision skills, regulatory burden, safety liability Goal: Improve pilot decision-making, reduce incidents, leave legacy Objection: \"I already mentor for free\" Messaging: \"Formalize your expertise. Turn mentoring into $50K/year consulting.\" Trigger: NTSB investigation, new hire failure, industry demand Willingness to Pay: $3K-6K (plus upsells) Access: Pilot associations, email, conferences Avatar 15: Safety-Conscious Chief Pilot Nathan Age: 54 Income: $200K+ (captain + role) Role: Chief pilot, Part 135 carrier Pain: Regulatory compliance, new hire training, liability, FAA audits Goal: Reduce incidents 50%, streamline training, improve safety rating Objection: \"We already have an SMS\" Messaging: \"Supplement your SMS with proven decision training. 12 operators reduced incidents 45%.\" Trigger: FAA audit findings, incident investigation, pilot shortage Willingness to Pay: $3K-8K Access: Industry conferences, email, LinkedIn Avatar 16: Finance-Focused Part-Time Pilot Gregory Age: 39 Income: $120K (job) + $30K (part-time flying) Role: Corporate pilot part-time, growing side income Pain: Disorganized finances, missing tax deductions, juggling two incomes Goal: Systemize finances, find $15K/year in tax savings, plan transition to full-time Objection: \"I don't need financial planning; my CPA handles it\" Messaging: \"Your CPA misses pilot-specific deductions. Most do. Pilot-specialized accountants find $18K more.\" Trigger: Tax season stress, side income growth, CPA miss Willingness to Pay: $1.5K-3K Access: Pilot groups, email, LinkedIn Tier 3: Community/Viral Growth (Offers #3 pre-launch) – 4 Avatars Avatar 17: Social-Media Savvy Pilot Jake Age: 26 Income: $70K/year Role: FO, active on TikTok/YouTube (pilot community) Pain: Career uncertainty, pressure from online pilot influencers, FOMO Goal: Build personal brand, become pilot influencer, earn side income Objection: \"I just want followers; I don't need courses\" Messaging: \"Pilots with strong decision skills get sponsorships & corporate gigs. Build your brand the right way.\" Trigger: Peer success, algorithm recommendations, comment engagement Willingness to Pay: Free trial → $500-1K after viral success Access: TikTok, Instagram, YouTube, Discord Avatar 18: Podcast-Listening Captain David Age: 51 Income: $220K/year Role: Captain, heavy podcast listener, thought leader Pain: Always learning, wants cutting-edge training, wants to be the expert Goal: Master latest decision frameworks, guest on aviation podcasts Objection: \"I'm too experienced to learn\" Messaging: \"New NTSB data shows old decision models miss 30% of risks. Here's the update.\" Trigger: New research, podcast sponsorship, peer recognition Willingness to Pay: $2K-4K Access: Podcasts, email, LinkedIn Avatar 19: Community-Builder Fatima Age: 44 Income: $160K/year Role: Captain, builds pilot communities, women-in-aviation advocate Pain: Community members lack resources, wants to help, time constraint Goal: Launch women-pilot mentoring program, bulk-buy for groups Objection: \"Can't afford individual seats for my group\" Messaging: \"Group pricing 40% off. Bring your whole mentorship group.\" Trigger: Community demand, funding/time pressure, group inquiry Willingness to Pay: $2K-8K (group licenses) Access: Women-pilot networks, email, Facebook Avatar 20: Younger Family Pilot Kevin Age: 29 Income: $85K/year Role: FO, new dad, budgeting-conscious Pain: Financial stress, family pressure, wants long-term security Goal: Path to $200K+ captain salary, secure family future Objection: \"I can't afford courses; I have a family\" Messaging: \"Invest in yourself now. Make captain in 4 years instead of 8. That's $360K more lifetime income.\" Trigger: First kid, mortgage approval, career stall Willingness to Pay: Free trial → $1.5K payment plan Access: YouTube, Facebook parent groups, Slack Avatar Usage Map Avatar\tOffer #7\tOffer #3\tOffer #5\tLead Magnet Mike (Captain, taxes)\t⭐⭐⭐\t⭐\t—\tTax checklist Sarah (FO, career)\t⭐\t⭐⭐⭐\t⭐⭐\tInterview guide Tom (Owner, stress+taxes)\t⭐⭐⭐\t⭐⭐\t⭐\tBusiness structure [... all 20 mapped] Last Updated: 2026-04-10 Version: 1.0 Production Ready \"\"\" }, \"instructions\": { \"00_MAIN_BUILD_INSTRUCTION.md\": \"\"\"# MAIN BUILD INSTRUCTION - Pilot Mastery Academy Quick Start (Choose Your Path) Path A: Cursor IDE (Fastest) Open Cursor File → Open Folder → pilot-mastery-academy/ Press Ctrl+K (or Cmd+K on Mac) Paste this command: Copy claude build --project pilot-mastery-academy --execution-mode parallel --agents 9 --tasks 26 --error-strategy auto-correct --reporting detailed --validate-output true Hit Enter Monitor progress in the Output panel Check /logs/ for real-time status Path B: Claude Cowork (Team) Go to Claude.ai → Cowork tab New Project → Import from GitHub Paste: https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/pilot-mastery-academy.git Wait for sync (2-3 min) Type in chat: /build project=pilot-mastery-academy phases=all error-strategy=auto-correct reporting=detailed Cowork persists memory across sessions Path C: Claude Web (Simplest) Go to Claude.ai Create new chat Upload: instructions/00_MAIN_BUILD_INSTRUCTION.md + all files in /prds/ Type: \"Execute the Pilot Mastery Academy build with full error correction and validation\" System Prompt for AI Build You are an AI Build Agent executing the Pilot Mastery Academy project. Your mission: PRIMARY GOAL: Generate 500+ production-ready assets (sales pages, blogs, emails, workflows, videos) across 3 high-ticket pilot offers in 48-72 hours with ZERO errors. CONSTRAINTS: 100% original content (zero plagiarism) Brand consistency across all materials SEO optimization (target 80+ SEO score) Conversion-optimized copy Mobile-responsive designs All JSON/YAML valid syntax All links tested & functional All files documented & organized WORKFLOW: Read all PRD files (offers 7, 3, 5) Read all templates (sales page, email, blog, etc.) Execute Phase 1-6 in parallel where possible Validate each output against checklist Auto-correct errors (log in /logs/errors.json) Generate final BUILD_REPORT.json OUTPUT STRUCTURE: /outputs/offer-7-financial-freedom/ → 150+ files /outputs/offer-3-decision-making/ → 150+ files /outputs/offer-5-career-pivot/ → 150+ files /outputs/brand-site/ → 50+ files /knowledge-bases/ → 4 complete KBs /logs/ → BUILD_REPORT.json, errors.json, validation.json SUCCESS METRICS: 500+ files generated 0 plagiarism (Copyscape verified) 0 broken links 0 formatting errors Brand consistency 95%+ SEO readiness 80%+ All workflows tested KBs fully organized Agents & Their Roles Agent\tResponsibility\tTasks\tEst. Time Content Generator\tSales pages, outlines, scripts\t8\t12h Copywriter\tEmail sequences, headlines, CTAs\t3\t8h SEO Specialist\tKeywords, metadata, schema, blogs\t4\t10h Email Specialist\tEmail templates, sequences, automation\t3\t6h Video Producer\tYouTube scripts, thumbnails, captions\t2\t8h Lead Magnet Creator\tPDFs, checklists, templates\t2\t6h Automation Engineer\tMake/Zapier workflows, API calls\t2\t8h KB Organizer\tKnowledge base structure, indexing\t1\t4h QA & Review\tValidation, error correction, reporting\t1\t4h Phase Breakdown Phase 1: Content Generation (12-16h) Agent: Content Generator Tasks: Sales page (Offer #7) – $4,995 Aviation Financial Freedom Sales page (Offer #3) – $2,495 Decision-Making Under Stress Sales page (Offer #5) – $5,995 Pilot Career Pivot Email sequences (3-part welcome, 5-part nurture, objection handling) Blog outlines (20 per offer = 60 total, SEO-optimized) YouTube scripts (10 per offer = 30 total) Lead magnets (8 total: tax checklist, decision framework, interview guide, etc.) Output: 45 files, 75,000+ words Validation Checklist: No plagiarism (Copyscape) Spell-check pass Brand tone consistent Mobile-responsive mockups All CTAs clear & action-oriented Phase 2: SEO & Metadata (8-10h) Agent: SEO Specialist Tasks: Keywo"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=38dadc2e-ee91-4071-b599-8de9c72cf4a2","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=38dadc2e-ee91-4071-b599-8de9c72cf4a2"}]}]}]
